Fix EM_AARCH64 not defined on old elf.h headers

Older toolchain elf.h headers may not define EM_AARCH64.
Add a fallback definition with the standard value (183).

Signed-off-by: nurikk <nurikk@users.noreply.github.com>
--- a/src/corelib/plugin/qelfparser_p.cpp
+++ b/src/corelib/plugin/qelfparser_p.cpp
@@ -20,6 +20,11 @@
 #  error "Need ELF header to parse plugins."
 #endif

+// EM_AARCH64 may not be defined in older elf.h headers
+#ifndef EM_AARCH64
+#  define EM_AARCH64 183
+#endif
+
 QT_BEGIN_NAMESPACE

 using namespace Qt::StringLiterals;
